    Port speech-to-text JWT auth: gate History on token + auto-attach Bearer
    
    Mirrors the SSO pattern from the speech-to-text repo:
      parent (MeetMind) postMessage "MEETMIND_AUTH" → child stores JWT
      in memory + localStorage → every API call carries
      Authorization: Bearer <token> automatically.
    
    When no token is held, the Saved Sessions drawer renders a sign-in
    placeholder instead of the list. Live transcription, AI Insights,
    the concept drawer, and full-session recording all keep working
    unauthenticated — only the saved-history list is gated, exactly
    the way speech-to-text gates its history.
    
    Files
    - frontend/src/auth.js (new) — port of speech-to-text auth.js with
      three additions for the LIVE codebase:
        1. fetch-based authFetch() helper (LIVE uses fetch, not axios),
        2. subscribe()/notify pattern so React components can re-render
           on token change without prop drilling,
        3. dev-only window.__liveAuth handle (tree-shaken in prod) so
           you can flip auth state from DevTools without a reload.
    - frontend/src/hooks/useAuthToken.js (new) — useSyncExternalStore
      subscription to the auth.js singleton, returns the current token
      with concurrent-mode-safe snapshot semantics.
    - frontend/src/main.jsx — imports auth.js as the FIRST import so
      the postMessage listener is registered on window before any
      React render. Without this ordering, a MEETMIND_AUTH message
      arriving during the first frame can be dropped, leaving the
      user permanently unauthenticated until they reload.
    - frontend/src/hooks/useSessionPersistence.js — every protected
      endpoint (POST /start-session, /push, /insights, /upload-audio,
      GET /transcripts, GET /transcript/:id, DELETE /transcript/:id)
      goes through authFetch instead of fetch. Public GET / health
      probe stays on plain fetch by design (it returns server
      diagnostics that should be visible to all visitors).
    - frontend/src/components/SessionHistory.jsx — new
      isAuthenticated prop. When false:
        * count badge shows 🔒 instead of N,
        * Refresh button is disabled,
        * subtitle reads "Sign in to view your saved meetings.",
        * a SignInPlaceholder card replaces the entire list (rather
          than rendering an empty/error state) and explains how to
          authenticate via MeetMind.
      When true the drawer behaves exactly as before. The list is
      also cleared when authentication is dropped, so a logged-out
      user can never glimpse cached entries from a previous session.
    - frontend/src/App.jsx — uses useAuthToken() to derive
      isAuthenticated, prefixes the History header button with 🔒
      when locked, threads isAuthenticated into <SessionHistory/>.
      Updated tooltip explains why the button is locked.
    
    Env var
      VITE_MEETMIND_ORIGIN — exact origin of the MeetMind parent
                              window (no trailing slash). Defaults to
                              https://meetmind.vercel.app. The strict
                              equality check rejects any postMessage
                              coming from any other origin, even if it
                              contains a valid-looking token payload.
    
    Backend unchanged
    The HTTP API doesn't currently verify the JWT (out of scope for
    this PR — the user only asked for the FRONTEND gate). The
    Authorization header is sent on every protected request anyway,
    so the backend can start verifying it later without another
    frontend roll-out.
    
    Local-dev workflow
    Without a real MeetMind to send a postMessage, you can flip the
    state from DevTools:
    
      // dev-only console handle
      __liveAuth.setToken("dev-token")
      __liveAuth.clearToken()
    
      // works in prod too via raw localStorage
      localStorage.setItem("live_auth_token", "dev-token")
      location.reload()
    
    Build clean: 251 kB JS / 77 kB gzipped (+ ~1 kB for auth + hook +
    SignInPlaceholder).

